node.text: It’s the city of love and I promise to pant like a dog, get rained on, recite pi digits, and get self-consciously vulnerable... all the moves for a solid first date! For this episode of the Question Game, @bumble is donating to @stopaapihate @heartofdinner for me!! (now THATS a sexy move) #bumblepartner #aapiheritagemonth

node.title: Let’s go on a Date in #Paris

node.text: I got to surprise interview sweet @official.alankim for @caaamplify segment celebrating AAPI... and it was pretty much the most healing thing for me in months! Here are some clips and outtakes to bring you all the joy and hope that Alan gave me 😊🎬 Thanks to @creativeartistsagency for prioritizing awareness and progress through these town halls, to @kevhlin for spearheading this and so much more, and to all the speakers in the #CAAamplify ‘Confronting Asian-American Racism’ event (Link in bio to hear and learn from them all). Let’s all keep uplifting and listening to each other through this time. And please do watch @minarimovie ❤️ #stopasianhate

node.text: 3 deadly shootings targeting Asian Women in Atlanta yesterday. I couldn’t sleep. Some of these 5am ramblings are very personal, but I decided to share because ENOUGH IS ENOUGH. I hope this helps someone feel not so alone in all this muck. Allies, thank you and please watch til end, this is societal programming that we can change.

... and also that I’m not always the best at reading the fine print 🤷🏻‍♀️. And there’s always some sneaky hidden fee or gotcha in there.  I’ve teamed up with @affirm this holiday season to focus on Gifts... not Gotchas. No hidden fees. Ever.  Affirm is giving away one million dollars… $10,000 to 100 people who submit their own creative rendition of the absurd fine print in your life… a dramatic reading, song, rap, anything! Head to the link in my bio for more info!

NoPurchNec. 50 US&DC 18+ or the age of majority in state of residence as of 11/19/20. Ends 12/10/20. Void where prohibited. Contest not affiliated with Instagram Rules&Enter: www.affirm.com/giftsnotgotchas #GiftsnotGotcha

node.text:
•I’ve just realized that this was the last time I sang live for an audience, and realistically, the last time I’ll sing for this many people in one room for a very long time 😔
•
I was just sent this video of my National Anthem at MSG from back in March. It was three days before Broadway and the country shut down. It was International women’s day (an all-women team from the NYC police department are standing alongside me), and I almost pulled out of singing that day, feeling run-over and unwell after finishing GRAND HORIZONS that week, the last show to officially close on Broadway before the shutdown... But I’d never sang at MSG, and for a Michigan gal living in New York, how could I pass up singing at the Detroit Pistons VS. New York Knicks game?! I hesitated sharing this video because I can tell how tired and stressed I was (thank you @justiewolf for doing my hair and love-shoving me onto that court).
•
But as I listen to the lyrics of our National Anthem again, I hear the BATTLECRY in the words that paved our country with a new fire. It’s about HOPE and RESILIENCE when there seems to be none. We MUST exercise our voices with hope and fervor. We must VOTE so that our country can be led in this dire time, to truly be a proud “land of the free, and the home of the brave.” #vote #bidenharris2020 💙🙏🏻🤟🏼🇺🇸

node.text:
How was this one year ago?? @lilyjcollins ❤️ swipe for bts...
As we go into our last weeks shooting @emilyinparis, Im remembering how even the thought of filming Season 2 felt impossible and distant in the moments we made this video, struggling through our first tiktok venture, retreated and isolated on @andymanf @ericwomack ranch in the height of pandemic.

I hope all of you are doing okay as we make all sorts of transitions back into our world and work, and in moments when life feels too overwhelming to grasp, I hope we all still find ways to laugh. And thanks for always making that easy Lils 🌼

node.text: Made this for our parents, but I’m sharing bc i miss her so much already and I can’t believe we actually did this. My sisters first time in paris. And our first time ever in a foreign city together. What!! @audreyhehepark thanks for being the coolest little (but taller) sister ever 🤍 ps- i fully trip and fall at the end

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Ashley Park on July 13, 2021 tagging @televisionacad, @netflix, @lilyjcollins, and @emilyinparis. May be an image of 2 people, people sitting and text that says 'PRODUCER CAST'.

node.text: OMG!! @Emilyinparis is Emmy-nominated for “Outstanding Comedy Series”! Here’s us, moments after finding out today! Thanks to @televisionacad, our whole show family, and every one of you who found joy in watching our show... Truly can’t believe we got to find out on set together @lilyjcollins, every step of this ride is beautiful alongside you ❤️

Photo by Ashley Park on July 13, 2021. May be an image of 2 people and people standing.

Photo shared by Ashley Park on July 09, 2021 tagging @adeleblim. May be an image of 2 people and text that says 'HOME FILM NEWS July 9, 2021 9:00am PT Adele Lim Directing Ashley Park in Untitled R- Rated Comedy for Lionsgate, Point Grey (EXCLUSIVE) By Dave McNary, Brent Lang Timv.'.

node.text: AAYYYYE this is WILD ✨ My first lead ever is gonna be R-rated (sorry mom!) Feeling every kind of excitementttt... All-Asian Female creative team. All-Asian Female leads. @adeleblim you’re epically changing the game. @lionsgate @pointgrey @teresa.hsiao @cherrygrams thanks for trusting me 🥳  Now let’s rock and ROLLLL this fall!!!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Ashley Park on July 09, 2021 tagging @adeleblim. May be an image of 2 people and text that says 'HOME FILM NEWS July 9, 2021 9:00am PT Adele Lim Directing Ashley Park in Untitled R- Rated Comedy for Lionsgate, Point Grey (EXCLUSIVE) By Dave McNary, Brent Lang Timv.'.

Photo shared by Ashley Park on July 09, 2021 tagging @lionsgate, and @pointgrey. May be an image of text that says 'VARIETY Adele Lim, the writer of "Crazy Rich Asians" and "Raya and the Last Dragon," will make her directorial debut helming an untitled comedy for Lionsgate and Point Grey Pictures. The R-rated comedy will star Tony and Grammy-nominated actress Ashley Park ("Emily in Paris," "Girls 5Eva") and follows four Asian American women as they travel through Asia in search of one of their birth mothers. Along the way, their experience becomes one of bonding, friendship, belonging, and no-holds- barred wild debauchery that reveals the universal truth of what it means to know and love who you are.'.
Photo shared by Ashley Park on July 08, 2021 tagging @germanlarkin, and @giorgioarmani. May be an image of 1 person, standing and footwear.

node.text: Merci @giorgioarmani and team 🖤 to experience the return of in-person art at my first Paris #HauteCouture show, took my breath away 🥺 To be able to tangibly feel creative energy and applaud a legend/artist in the same room again, with such lovely company... I’m just so grateful and my heart is fully SWOLLEN thinking of when we’ll get to be in the live audience of a Broadway theater, etc. 🦋 thanks to my Emily In Paris team @_carolenicolas_ @audettelm for quick-changing Mindy/me on set, and to @germanlarkin for this special photo diary!

node.text:
Please excuse this musical-theatre Broadway-lovin GEEEEK as I dance around alone in a Paris living room and maybe weep over this pinch-me moment 🤓💃🏻🥰 To be honored in this way means so much to me @laducashoes, especially since it’s been so long since I and so many of us have been able to dance on a stage with our friends.
I remember trying on my first pair of LaDucas as a teen, and not feeling worthy or cool enough to dance in them or be on a #Broadway stage 🥺 But I encourage you, and remind myself, not to get in our own way by judging ourselves before we can even try. My Laducas have gotten me through years of auditions, rehearsals, successes, rejections, falls, leaps, shows, and the occasional Halloween costume. I’m grateful for every one of these memories while humbled by this full-circle moment. Still can’t do a clean triple pirouette 🙆🏻‍♀️, but hell, this ‘Gretchen’ heel feels pretty fetch 💕

node.text: 💘🪁🍾🌷♊️ just want to say thank you all so much for the beautiful birthday wishes, sending huge hugs far and wide!! to my loved ones who I’m homesick for, and to those in Paris with me who made stepping into this next chapter so exciting and supported (esp lookin at you @lilyjcollins) 🤍 special merci @loulourestaurant and @nabilanad for a lovely eve 🌅
